#week-title("Four", "Elemental Meditations & Albedo Integration")

=== Core Teaching

This week focus on the *Elemental Meditations*. These are not visualisation
exercises, but practices of direct perceptual attention trained on each element
as a living reality.

The alchemist must be as familiar with the elements in the macrocosm as they are
with their expressions in the flask. This month's work has been about the
transition to the Albedo — the washing away of the blackness.

=== Topics This Week

- Direct perception of Earth, Water, Air, and Fire
- Reviewing the Albedo transition in the journal
- Preparation for Quarter III Gathering

#inner-work[
  *Elemental Meditations*

  Practice each of the following this week:
  - *Earth:* Sit on the ground. Attend to solidity, weight, and stillness.
  - *Water:* Sit near water. Attend to flow, reflection, and depth.
  - *Air:* Sit in the wind. Attend to breath, movement, and the invisible.
  - *Fire:* Sit with a candle. Attend to illumination and the *Secret Fire*.

  Record your experiences. How do these elements appear in your Melissa
  distillation?
]

